OL,4,Cstill "has no plans to resign" over
OL,5,Coutages
OL,7,FAsked if he has reconsidered his
OL,8,Fposition, Mr Hinton said: "The plan
OL,9,Fneeds to get delivered. We could
OL,10,Fchange the leadership team of the
OL,11,Fcompany, but the plan will be the plan.
OL,13,F"So that's what we should be
OL,14,Fabsolutely focusing on, is that the
OL,15,Fplan needs to get delivered."
OL,17,F"I understand the frustration of our
OL,18,Fcustomers, I really, really do.
OL,20,F"And again, I'm sorry for what they
OL,21,Fwent through.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/14
